The paper focuses on convolutional neural networks (CNNs) for computational imaging tasks, which are typically related to computer vision (cs.CV) and augmented reality (cs.AR). The paper also addresses hardware constraints and optimization, which could fall under human-computer interaction (cs.HC) and multimedia (cs.MM). Finally, the paper discusses the use of block-based inference, which could be relevant to systems and control (cs.SY).
